1
00:01:33,840 --> 00:01:36,760
The color difference between these two versions

2
00:01:37,240 --> 00:01:39,000
should be around 0.003.

3
00:01:41,400 --> 00:01:42,640
0.003.

4
00:01:43,920 --> 00:01:44,840
No more, no less.

5
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:46,600
Exactly 0.003.

6
00:01:46,600 --> 00:01:48,480
Lao Huang, don't get worked up just yet.

7
00:01:49,120 --> 00:01:51,360
There's always someone better out there.

8
00:01:51,360 --> 00:01:53,120
Mr. Xin, that's not how it works.

9
00:01:53,880 --> 00:01:56,280
A 0.003 color difference, you know what that means?

10
00:01:56,280 --> 00:01:57,960
That's on the micrometer scale.

11
00:01:59,160 --> 00:02:01,160
If you put these two rulers side by side,

12
00:02:01,320 --> 00:02:03,520
only a thousandth of a millimeter apart.

13
00:02:03,840 --> 00:02:06,520
Mr. Xuan just stated very precisely

14
00:02:06,800 --> 00:02:08,479
it's a difference of three-thousandths.

15
00:02:09,160 --> 00:02:11,039
If you can really spot that difference,

16
00:02:11,240 --> 00:02:12,280
then I'll be damned.

17
00:02:12,280 --> 00:02:13,920
Fine, Manager Huang, let's stop arguing.

18
00:02:13,920 --> 00:02:14,680
How about this.

19
00:02:14,720 --> 00:02:16,920
If my judgment turns out to be wrong,

20
00:02:17,000 --> 00:02:19,520
I'll throw a banquet and apologize in person.

21
00:02:19,520 --> 00:02:20,240
Alright.

22
00:02:20,760 --> 00:02:21,520
Deal.

23
00:02:21,520 --> 00:02:22,840
Then we'll take these and compare them.

24
00:02:22,880 --> 00:02:24,120
Please have a seat for a moment.

25
00:02:29,120 --> 00:02:30,200
You're going too?

26
00:02:34,920 --> 00:02:35,720
Sit down.

27
00:02:40,040 --> 00:02:41,000
Do you even know what you're doing?

28
00:02:41,240 --> 00:02:42,080
If you're going to embarrass yourself,

29
00:02:42,080 --> 00:02:43,280
don't drag me into it, okay?

30
00:02:43,280 --> 00:02:44,000
Come on,

31
00:02:44,120 --> 00:02:46,320
am I really that unreliable in your eyes?

32
00:02:46,680 --> 00:02:47,920
Have you ever been reliable?

33
00:02:52,200 --> 00:02:54,040
A color difference of only 0.003 between two samples?

34
00:02:54,120 --> 00:02:55,160
How is that possible?

35
00:02:55,680 --> 00:02:56,840
Let the data speak.

36
00:03:01,080 --> 00:03:01,960
The results are in.

37
00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:04,560
What results?

38
00:03:11,320 --> 00:03:12,200
How did it go?

39
00:03:28,400 --> 00:03:29,040
Looks like

40
00:03:29,920 --> 00:03:31,400
I'll have to take you as my master.

41
00:03:35,880 --> 00:03:36,640
Master.

42
00:03:38,440 --> 00:03:39,240
Manager Huang,

43
00:03:39,480 --> 00:03:41,080
my skills are just for show.

44
00:03:41,200 --> 00:03:42,320
Your old techniques and experience

45
00:03:42,320 --> 00:03:44,040
are what I should learn from.

46
00:03:44,360 --> 00:03:45,720
The younger generation is formidable.

47
00:03:47,920 --> 00:03:49,000
The results are in.

48
00:03:51,040 --> 00:03:51,920
What results?

49
00:03:57,160 --> 00:03:58,000
Try it again.

50
00:03:58,000 --> 00:04:00,360
This precision machine has zero error.

51
00:04:00,360 --> 00:04:01,240
Get out of the way.

52
00:04:01,720 --> 00:04:02,680
No margin of error.

53
00:04:06,040 --> 00:04:07,680
The result is still 0.003.

54
00:04:11,320 --> 00:04:12,920
You all saw it, didn't you?

55
00:04:13,320 --> 00:04:15,920
Master Xuan's eyes really are razor-sharp.

56
00:04:16,320 --> 00:04:18,320
So when we go into mass production,

57
00:04:18,320 --> 00:04:20,440
you must keep strict quality control.

58
00:04:20,600 --> 00:04:22,440
Not even the slightest deviation.

59
00:04:22,440 --> 00:04:23,160
Yes.

60
00:04:23,200 --> 00:04:24,040
Master Xuan,

61
00:04:24,200 --> 00:04:26,160
shall we continue discussing cooperation?

62
00:04:33,440 --> 00:04:34,040
Sure.

63
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:35,920
Let's continue.

64
00:04:39,920 --> 00:04:40,760
Please, have a seat.

65
00:04:45,200 --> 00:04:45,840
Old Xuan!

66
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:48,640
Old Xuan!

67
00:04:52,520 --> 00:04:54,240
That thing Miss Lin mentioned last time,

68
00:04:54,240 --> 00:04:56,400
the Xuan paper notebook deal, it's done!

69
00:04:57,240 --> 00:05:00,040
Dayazhai ordered a ton of Jingpi paper first.

70
00:05:00,040 --> 00:05:01,320
The money's in the account.

71
00:05:01,320 --> 00:05:04,040
They'll order another ton in a month.

72
00:05:05,640 --> 00:05:08,040
Oh my, that's two tons!

73
00:05:08,680 --> 00:05:10,240
Then we'll have to work overtime.

74
00:05:11,120 --> 00:05:12,360
There's money to be made and he's complaining?

75
00:05:12,360 --> 00:05:14,240
Is there something wrong with his head?

76
00:05:14,240 --> 00:05:15,120
Exactly.

77
00:05:15,120 --> 00:05:15,880
With business booming,

78
00:05:15,880 --> 00:05:17,800
we're happy to work overtime!

79
00:05:17,800 --> 00:05:19,600
Let's just get to it right away.

80
00:05:19,600 --> 00:05:20,320
That's right.

81
00:05:20,560 --> 00:05:22,280
I'll handle the logistics.

82
00:05:23,280 --> 00:05:24,120
You hear that?

83
00:05:24,280 --> 00:05:26,320
At night, put that phone of yours away.

84
00:05:26,320 --> 00:05:27,280
Focus on scooping paper.

85
00:05:27,600 --> 00:05:28,520
I got it.

86
00:05:28,680 --> 00:05:29,880
And put away those cigarettes too.

87
00:05:31,000 --> 00:05:32,600
Working overtime, fine.

88
00:05:32,720 --> 00:05:33,760
But you all

89
00:05:33,960 --> 00:05:35,880
have to get me a pair of reading glasses.

90
00:05:36,200 --> 00:05:37,000
Sure.

91
00:05:37,440 --> 00:05:38,880
I'll get you a pair then,

92
00:05:39,120 --> 00:05:40,920
those celebrity-style aviator shades.

93
00:05:41,000 --> 00:05:41,880
Then wouldn't I look like

94
00:05:41,880 --> 00:05:44,000
the bandit chief from "Wulong Mountain Bandit Suppression,"

95
00:05:44,000 --> 00:05:44,920
Tian Dabang?

96
00:05:44,920 --> 00:05:45,680
Let me see.

97
00:05:45,880 --> 00:05:46,720
You know what, it really does look alike.

98
00:05:46,720 --> 00:05:47,680
If you put them on...

99
00:06:02,880 --> 00:06:03,880
Here, give me one.

100
00:06:08,120 --> 00:06:09,120
How does it feel?

101
00:06:13,160 --> 00:06:14,000
Just about right.

102
00:06:34,360 --> 00:06:36,240
All handmade. How about it?

103
00:06:36,800 --> 00:06:37,640
Professional.

104
00:06:48,440 --> 00:06:51,360
The key here is even edges.

105
00:06:52,240 --> 00:06:53,000
No problem, right?

106
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:09,360
Comrades,

107
00:07:09,440 --> 00:07:12,720
from this Xuan paper notebook phenomenon,

108
00:07:12,760 --> 00:07:14,040
we should draw inspiration.

109
00:07:14,800 --> 00:07:17,240
It's not that our Xuan paper industry is failing,

110
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:19,840
it's that we haven't opened our minds.

111
00:07:20,200 --> 00:07:23,120
We must dig deep into its potential value.

112
00:07:23,360 --> 00:07:23,920
Just think about it.

113
00:07:23,920 --> 00:07:26,560
The Wannianhong couplets are loved by the people.

114
00:07:26,560 --> 00:07:27,080
Right.

115
00:07:27,080 --> 00:07:29,760
Dayazhai's thread-bound books were a hit.

116
00:07:30,440 --> 00:07:33,680
Now we've developed Xuan paper notebooks,

117
00:07:34,760 --> 00:07:36,280
which are getting lots of attention.

118
00:07:36,960 --> 00:07:38,840
So, comrades,

119
00:07:39,040 --> 00:07:40,400
we must develop

120
00:07:40,400 --> 00:07:42,720
more products that the public loves,

121
00:07:42,840 --> 00:07:46,280
products that can reach every household,

122
00:07:46,360 --> 00:07:48,080
Xuan paper cultural products.

123
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:48,960
Exactly.

124
00:07:49,520 --> 00:07:50,080
Old Liao,

125
00:07:51,040 --> 00:07:52,280
what I just said,

126
00:07:52,280 --> 00:07:55,080
about digging deep into Xuan paper's potential value

127
00:07:55,240 --> 00:07:56,320
and expanding the market,

128
00:07:56,560 --> 00:07:57,440
on this,

129
00:07:57,440 --> 00:07:58,760
you need to put more heart into it.

130
00:07:59,200 --> 00:08:00,680
Help me lead

131
00:08:00,920 --> 00:08:01,800
the team of young folks.

132
00:08:01,880 --> 00:08:02,480
Alright.

133
00:08:04,840 --> 00:08:06,680
But do they really need me to lead them?

134
00:08:07,240 --> 00:08:08,600
Of course we need you.

135
00:08:08,840 --> 00:08:10,120
The young ones

136
00:08:10,360 --> 00:08:12,480
certainly have drive and energy,

137
00:08:12,520 --> 00:08:13,160
but,

138
00:08:13,160 --> 00:08:14,600
we veteran comrades

139
00:08:14,760 --> 00:08:15,560
have experience,

140
00:08:15,760 --> 00:08:16,960
we're steady and dependable.

141
00:08:17,480 --> 00:08:19,680
We need veterans like you

142
00:08:19,840 --> 00:08:22,280
to steer the young ones in the right direction.

143
00:08:23,280 --> 00:08:24,520
Thank you, Secretary Peng.

144
00:08:26,960 --> 00:08:28,520
Since Secretary Peng brought this up,

145
00:08:28,840 --> 00:08:29,920
let me say a few words.

146
00:08:29,920 --> 00:08:30,480
Go ahead.

147
00:08:31,240 --> 00:08:32,919
The Xuan paper notebook

148
00:08:33,840 --> 00:08:36,159
has received Secretary Peng's recognition and attention.

149
00:08:36,559 --> 00:08:39,120
We had President An promote it at the fair

150
00:08:39,760 --> 00:08:41,120
and brought in quite a few orders.

151
00:08:41,799 --> 00:08:43,240
I hope

152
00:08:44,080 --> 00:08:47,520
everyone views this fact objectively.

153
00:08:48,120 --> 00:08:49,440
I hope everyone is clear

154
00:08:49,920 --> 00:08:53,880
that this is just an isolated case.

155
00:08:55,120 --> 00:08:56,280
As for how much market impact

156
00:08:56,440 --> 00:08:58,600
this notebook can actually bring

157
00:08:59,080 --> 00:09:00,600
to our Taohua Town,

158
00:09:00,680 --> 00:09:04,800
I hope everyone calms down,

159
00:09:04,840 --> 00:09:05,680
cools off a bit,

160
00:09:06,480 --> 00:09:07,720
and views it objectively.

161
00:09:15,400 --> 00:09:17,640
Director Liao loves playing the stern judge.

162
00:09:17,880 --> 00:09:18,640
He's our town's

163
00:09:18,640 --> 00:09:20,360
famous unofficial disciplinary chief.

164
00:09:20,720 --> 00:09:21,600
You're both right.

165
00:09:22,400 --> 00:09:23,800
We can't be arrogant,

166
00:09:24,360 --> 00:09:26,600
but we can't underestimate ourselves either.

167
00:09:27,600 --> 00:09:31,040
Right, we must be realistic.

168
00:09:31,520 --> 00:09:32,760
Secretary Peng is right.

169
00:09:33,200 --> 00:09:34,560
Speaking of being realistic,

170
00:09:34,560 --> 00:09:36,760
Secretary Peng, let me be frank.

171
00:09:36,760 --> 00:09:37,400
Go ahead.

172
00:09:39,040 --> 00:09:42,040
While handling the notebook deal,

173
00:09:43,720 --> 00:09:45,200
quite a few problems came up.

174
00:09:46,080 --> 00:09:47,520
Then tell us about them.

175
00:09:48,200 --> 00:09:49,840
We've taken many notebook orders,

176
00:09:50,520 --> 00:09:51,800
all went to the Xuan family.

177
00:09:52,240 --> 00:09:53,920
What about other mills? Any complaints?

178
00:09:56,240 --> 00:09:57,520
The Xuan paper notebooks

179
00:09:57,520 --> 00:09:59,400
were originally designed by Xuan Yan.

180
00:09:59,520 --> 00:10:01,240
He has very high quality standards,

181
00:10:01,240 --> 00:10:03,800
so he's only authorized Dayazhai for now.

182
00:10:03,960 --> 00:10:05,040
Other mills can't produce them.

183
00:10:05,720 --> 00:10:08,000
You can tell me that,

184
00:10:08,440 --> 00:10:10,480
but other mill owners won't accept it.

185
00:10:10,480 --> 00:10:12,400
But the issue now is,

186
00:10:12,400 --> 00:10:15,200
if Xuan Yan doesn't authorize or approve,

187
00:10:15,280 --> 00:10:17,040
then other mills simply can't make them.

188
00:10:17,880 --> 00:10:20,520
The client was brought in by President An

189
00:10:21,040 --> 00:10:22,520
through tremendous effort.

190
00:10:22,520 --> 00:10:23,520
For whose sake?

191
00:10:23,520 --> 00:10:25,880
For the entire Xuan paper industry

192
00:10:26,120 --> 00:10:27,960
of Taohua Town in Jing County,

193
00:10:28,840 --> 00:10:30,160
not just for the Xuan family.

194
00:10:30,360 --> 00:10:33,080
And Xuan Yan certainly can't have the final say.

195
00:10:33,120 --> 00:10:35,040
If other mills can't meet quality standards,

196
00:10:35,040 --> 00:10:36,640
Dayazhai wouldn't accept them either.

197
00:10:37,320 --> 00:10:39,040
Xuan Yan must have selfish motives.

198
00:10:39,480 --> 00:10:41,520
How will such words convince anyone?

199
00:10:42,320 --> 00:10:43,120
Lin Yiran,

200
00:10:43,640 --> 00:10:46,280
balance and coordinate all relationships,

201
00:10:46,280 --> 00:10:48,760
so no one has anything to complain about.

202
00:10:49,120 --> 00:10:50,440
That's your job,

203
00:10:50,440 --> 00:10:51,880
not arguing with me here.

204
00:10:51,880 --> 00:10:53,360
I'm not arguing.

205
00:10:53,520 --> 00:10:56,080
Some mills in the association are used to cutting corners,

206
00:10:56,080 --> 00:10:57,120
passing off inferior goods as quality.

207
00:10:57,280 --> 00:10:58,720
If we distribute these orders

208
00:10:58,720 --> 00:11:00,480
and they produce defective products,

209
00:11:00,480 --> 00:11:02,280
how will you answer to the higher-ups?

210
00:11:02,320 --> 00:11:04,080
Taohua Town's Xuan paper industry's image

211
00:11:04,240 --> 00:11:06,040
has been ruined by exactly these people!

212
00:11:06,960 --> 00:11:09,480
Lin Yiran, watch your words.

213
00:11:12,160 --> 00:11:14,840
I think Director Liao made a valid point.

214
00:11:15,000 --> 00:11:16,360
You should take it seriously

215
00:11:16,480 --> 00:11:18,000
and reflect on it carefully.

216
00:11:20,960 --> 00:11:22,800
Director Liao is your direct supervisor.

217
00:11:22,800 --> 00:11:24,560
Whatever he says, you should follow.

218
00:11:24,920 --> 00:11:26,440
Talking back to him in front of Secretary Peng,

219
00:11:26,440 --> 00:11:27,720
even if you're right, you're wrong.

220
00:11:28,320 --> 00:11:29,800
It was all for work.

221
00:11:29,920 --> 00:11:31,400
Why can't I speak up?

222
00:11:31,400 --> 00:11:32,560
If speaking has negative effects,

223
00:11:32,560 --> 00:11:33,560
it's better not to speak at all.

224
00:11:34,200 --> 00:11:36,080
Fine, I'm wrong again.

225
00:11:36,560 --> 00:11:37,440
Then tomorrow

226
00:11:37,800 --> 00:11:39,480
I'll apologize to him, okay?

227
00:11:39,600 --> 00:11:41,560
Deputy Mayor Luo used to work under him,

228
00:11:41,680 --> 00:11:43,000
then leapfrogged him into leadership

229
00:11:43,200 --> 00:11:44,440
and became his superior.

230
00:11:44,480 --> 00:11:45,680
With what you're doing now,

231
00:11:45,680 --> 00:11:46,320
in his eyes,

232
00:11:46,320 --> 00:11:47,960
you're just like Deputy Mayor Luo.

233
00:11:49,040 --> 00:11:50,120
No wonder.

234
00:11:50,560 --> 00:11:53,000
No wonder he keeps saying I'm too impatient.

235
00:11:53,440 --> 00:11:54,240
Exactly.

236
00:11:57,400 --> 00:11:57,960
Director Liao.

237
00:11:59,240 --> 00:12:00,040
Lin Yiran,

238
00:12:06,240 --> 00:12:07,360
Secretary Peng has spoken.

239
00:12:07,360 --> 00:12:09,600
He's telling you to revise and adjust.

240
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:10,840
No, no.

241
00:12:10,840 --> 00:12:12,040
Liao... Director Liao, tea.

242
00:12:12,040 --> 00:12:12,720
Liao...

243
00:12:25,640 --> 00:12:28,240
This draft Director Liao wrote,

244
00:12:28,440 --> 00:12:30,120
I don't see any problems with it.

245
00:12:30,240 --> 00:12:31,360
Looks pretty normal.

246
00:12:31,520 --> 00:12:32,320
Normal?

247
00:12:33,240 --> 00:12:35,480
If Secretary Peng assigned someone

248
00:12:35,480 --> 00:12:37,320
to take over all your work,

249
00:12:37,480 --> 00:12:38,600
would you think that's normal?

250
00:12:38,800 --> 00:12:40,800
Overstepping your role is a big taboo.

251
00:12:41,400 --> 00:12:42,880
Director Liao just said it himself,

252
00:12:43,120 --> 00:12:44,440
Secretary Peng gave the order.

253
00:12:44,560 --> 00:12:45,680
How is this my fault?

254
00:12:46,320 --> 00:12:47,520
Oh, my dear sister.

255
00:12:47,680 --> 00:12:49,000
Do you know who Director Liao is?

256
00:12:49,000 --> 00:12:51,000
A renowned teacher at the county high school.

257
00:12:51,240 --> 00:12:53,080
He's been published in the provincial paper.

258
00:12:53,400 --> 00:12:54,960
He thinks he's brimming with talent,

259
00:12:54,960 --> 00:12:56,480
that teaching was beneath him.

260
00:12:56,640 --> 00:12:58,480
So he took the civil exam to do PR here.

261
00:12:58,760 --> 00:13:00,680
Writing is his bread and butter.

262
00:13:01,160 --> 00:13:02,040
And now look,

263
00:13:02,560 --> 00:13:04,640
Secretary Peng wants you to revise his draft.

264
00:13:04,720 --> 00:13:06,520
Isn't that a huge slap in the face?

265
00:13:07,320 --> 00:13:08,160
I'm telling you,

266
00:13:08,720 --> 00:13:10,160
once this grudge takes root,

267
00:13:10,640 --> 00:13:11,880
you'll never untangle it.

268
00:13:12,280 --> 00:13:14,880
I'll just do what the boss asked of me.

269
00:13:14,880 --> 00:13:16,120
I can't worry about the rest.

270
00:13:16,440 --> 00:13:17,600
What does "doing it well" mean?

271
00:13:17,880 --> 00:13:20,840
Secretary Peng told you to revise it,

272
00:13:21,120 --> 00:13:22,960
but what she really wants

273
00:13:22,960 --> 00:13:25,160
is for you to handle everything smoothly.

274
00:13:25,240 --> 00:13:26,040
And that, of course,

275
00:13:26,320 --> 00:13:29,120
includes managing your rapport with Director Liao.

276
00:13:31,720 --> 00:13:32,760
Fine, I'll revise it well.

277
00:13:32,760 --> 00:13:34,160
I'll send it to Director Liao first,

278
00:13:34,160 --> 00:13:35,840
then forward it to Secretary Peng.

279
00:13:36,280 --> 00:13:37,640
Don't just send it to Director Liao.

280
00:13:38,160 --> 00:13:41,520
Print it out and humbly ask his advice.

281
00:13:43,640 --> 00:13:45,240
Isn't that a hassle?

282
00:13:51,160 --> 00:13:52,000
Delivery's here!

283
00:13:52,000 --> 00:13:53,160
Come grab your delivery.

284
00:13:54,520 --> 00:13:55,520
Delivery! Your delivery!

285
00:13:55,520 --> 00:13:56,520
Come get your delivery.

286
00:13:57,280 --> 00:13:58,400
Is this yours?

287
00:14:09,640 --> 00:14:10,760
Is this your delivery?

288
00:14:11,720 --> 00:14:13,120
You want it or not? I'm taking it.

289
00:14:13,880 --> 00:14:14,680
Delivery!

290
00:14:15,000 --> 00:14:16,240
Mine, mine, mine!

291
00:14:16,240 --> 00:14:16,840
Your delivery.

292
00:14:16,840 --> 00:14:18,120
Sorry, sorry, it's mine.

293
00:14:18,240 --> 00:14:19,000
Snail noodles, right?

294
00:14:19,000 --> 00:14:19,880
Yeah, snail noodles.

295
00:14:19,880 --> 00:14:20,360
Okay, thanks.

296
00:14:20,360 --> 00:14:21,400
Yep, your snail noodles. No problem.

297
00:14:25,760 --> 00:14:26,880
Want some snail noodles?

298
00:14:26,880 --> 00:14:27,880
The flavor's spot-on.

299
00:14:30,160 --> 00:14:31,520
Right, I forgot.

300
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:33,760
You don't like this smell.

301
00:14:33,760 --> 00:14:35,120
I even ordered an extra portion.

302
00:14:40,880 --> 00:14:42,120
Where's my tea bowl?

303
00:14:45,000 --> 00:14:46,480
Let me borrow your Jian cup.

304
00:14:46,600 --> 00:14:47,240
No way.

305
00:14:47,840 --> 00:14:48,640
Xuan Yan!

306
00:14:50,160 --> 00:14:51,240
No way, Xuan Yan.

307
00:14:52,720 --> 00:14:54,240
That stuff stinks too much. No way.

308
00:14:54,880 --> 00:14:56,520
Xuan Yan, Xuan Yan, no way.

309
00:14:56,520 --> 00:14:57,720
Your willpower's pretty weak.

310
00:14:57,720 --> 00:15:00,000
A bowl of snail noodles broke your zen.

311
00:15:00,400 --> 00:15:02,120
"Stir three rivers, not a sage's heart."

312
00:15:02,120 --> 00:15:03,240
Haven't you heard that saying?

313
00:15:03,240 --> 00:15:04,600
Stop putting yourself on a pedestal.

314
00:15:04,600 --> 00:15:05,640
If you were truly a sage,

315
00:15:05,640 --> 00:15:07,000
I couldn't break your zen at all.

316
00:15:08,600 --> 00:15:09,600
Let me use this one.

317
00:15:10,040 --> 00:15:11,000
No, no, no!

318
00:15:11,120 --> 00:15:12,640
My Dunhuang master made that one.

319
00:15:12,640 --> 00:15:13,960
Your Dunhuang master made this one.

320
00:15:13,960 --> 00:15:15,720
That one your Beijing master made.

321
00:15:15,840 --> 00:15:16,560
You keep going on and on.

322
00:15:16,560 --> 00:15:18,280
Just find me one I can actually use!

323
00:15:18,760 --> 00:15:20,720
Why do you need a cup for snail noodles?

324
00:15:20,720 --> 00:15:21,880
Don't I need water to drink?

325
00:15:24,720 --> 00:15:25,640
Come on, come on.

326
00:15:25,640 --> 00:15:26,640
Use this one, use this.

327
00:15:28,920 --> 00:15:29,720
Xuan Yan.

328
00:15:30,120 --> 00:15:32,120
I want to talk something over with you.

329
00:15:32,760 --> 00:15:35,000
I'm thinking of starting a video channel.

330
00:15:35,400 --> 00:15:37,280
Focused on authentic traditional paper.

331
00:15:38,240 --> 00:15:41,000
On one hand, promote Xuan paper culture.

332
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:43,120
And on the other, do livestream sales.

333
00:15:43,880 --> 00:15:45,120
What do you think of the idea?

334
00:15:47,640 --> 00:15:48,560
What are you "hmm-ing" about?

335
00:15:48,560 --> 00:15:50,120
You haven't even grasped my plan yet.

336
00:15:50,400 --> 00:15:52,520
Your motives are obvious to everyone.

337
00:15:52,520 --> 00:15:54,240
The phrase might not quite fit here,

338
00:15:54,240 --> 00:15:56,120
but the meaning's close enough.

339
00:15:56,400 --> 00:15:58,640
Aren't you just trying to build yourself

340
00:16:00,120 --> 00:16:01,520
a guardian of heritage,

341
00:16:01,760 --> 00:16:03,600
master craftsman persona?

342
00:16:03,600 --> 00:16:04,760
Come on, bro.

343
00:16:04,840 --> 00:16:06,480
The era of big influencers selling goods

344
00:16:06,480 --> 00:16:07,760
is already over.

345
00:16:07,760 --> 00:16:09,840
Look, how many of them are still making money?

346
00:16:10,240 --> 00:16:12,000
I'm not doing it just for the money.

347
00:16:12,240 --> 00:16:15,520
My main responsibility is promoting the craft.

348
00:16:15,520 --> 00:16:17,400
Making money is making money, nothing shameful.

349
00:16:17,400 --> 00:16:19,760
Without money, how do you pass it on?

350
00:16:19,760 --> 00:16:21,000
True traditional paper

351
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:22,080
costs thousands per ream.

352
00:16:22,080 --> 00:16:22,760
Even if you turn yourself

353
00:16:22,760 --> 00:16:24,360
into some god descended from heaven,

354
00:16:24,360 --> 00:16:25,560
people still might not buy it.

355
00:16:27,400 --> 00:16:28,680
If you really want to make money,

356
00:16:28,680 --> 00:16:29,920
let me give you an idea.

357
00:16:29,920 --> 00:16:32,400
Keep the persona lofty and grand,

358
00:16:32,400 --> 00:16:33,680
the loftier the better.

359
00:16:33,800 --> 00:16:34,680
That kind of vibe,

360
00:16:35,160 --> 00:16:36,680
the grandmaster aura.

361
00:16:37,040 --> 00:16:39,680
But the actual sales price has to be cheap.

362
00:16:39,760 --> 00:16:40,680
Three yuan per sheet.

363
00:16:40,680 --> 00:16:42,200
Twenty percent off for ten, free shipping too.

364
00:16:43,000 --> 00:16:44,680
Isn't that just selling fake paper?

365
00:16:44,680 --> 00:16:44,920
No way.

366
00:16:44,920 --> 00:16:45,680
No, no, no.

367
00:16:45,880 --> 00:16:47,560
Just sell it as calligraphy paper.

368
00:16:47,800 --> 00:16:48,800
Look at the online platforms.

369
00:16:48,800 --> 00:16:50,440
The top sellers in revenue

370
00:16:50,920 --> 00:16:52,200
all rely on volume.

371
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:54,760
The data feedback is the most truthful.

372
00:16:54,800 --> 00:16:56,200
More reliable than your

373
00:16:56,200 --> 00:16:57,320
spur-of-the-moment ideas.

374
00:16:58,000 --> 00:16:59,040
Let me teach you another trick.

375
00:16:59,560 --> 00:17:01,040
While selling paper,

376
00:17:01,200 --> 00:17:02,560
teach people calligraphy and painting.

377
00:17:02,760 --> 00:17:04,880
Let them find enlightenment through art.

378
00:17:05,200 --> 00:17:07,760
With your face, plus a little beauty filter,

379
00:17:09,319 --> 00:17:12,160
I'm sure a whole bunch of women

380
00:17:12,280 --> 00:17:13,800
will follow you, adore you.

381
00:17:14,280 --> 00:17:15,160
What's this called?

382
00:17:15,280 --> 00:17:17,280
This is your traffic formula.

383
00:17:17,480 --> 00:17:18,280
Remember this.

384
00:17:18,280 --> 00:17:19,800
Making money comes down to one thing:

385
00:17:19,800 --> 00:17:20,920
the traffic economy.

386
00:17:20,920 --> 00:17:22,200
Once you grab the traffic,

387
00:17:22,200 --> 00:17:23,680
you've grabbed the wealth.

388
00:17:23,680 --> 00:17:24,560
Do you get it or not?

389
00:17:24,560 --> 00:17:26,400
If I follow your line of thinking,

390
00:17:26,640 --> 00:17:28,119
what meaning does life even have?

391
00:17:28,760 --> 00:17:30,400
Sounds like even living is a struggle for you.

392
00:17:30,920 --> 00:17:32,200
I don't believe that.

393
00:17:32,640 --> 00:17:34,640
Sticking to authentic craft inheritance,

394
00:17:34,800 --> 00:17:36,680
making quality paper,

395
00:17:36,800 --> 00:17:38,640
honest, fine Xuan paper,

396
00:17:38,640 --> 00:17:39,800
there's no way forward?

397
00:17:39,800 --> 00:17:40,600
None.

398
00:17:43,000 --> 00:17:45,280
There must be a small group in this world

399
00:17:45,280 --> 00:17:46,560
who will pay for a good sheet of paper,

400
00:17:46,560 --> 00:17:47,800
who will pay for the passion behind it.

401
00:17:47,800 --> 00:17:48,920
Yeah, those do exist.

402
00:17:48,920 --> 00:17:50,280
You wouldn't get two orders a month.

403
00:17:50,280 --> 00:17:51,440
Your master, my dad.

404
00:17:54,320 --> 00:17:55,680
I actually feel

405
00:17:56,040 --> 00:17:57,800
Master's approach isn't pure enough.

406
00:17:57,920 --> 00:17:58,880
Pure, huh?

407
00:17:59,680 --> 00:18:01,200
Then he'd die even more miserably.

408
00:18:07,400 --> 00:18:08,520
Now I get it.

409
00:18:08,880 --> 00:18:10,680
Traditional Xuan paper, in your hands,

410
00:18:10,920 --> 00:18:12,400
is doomed to die out.

411
00:18:13,920 --> 00:18:15,200
You're wrong.

412
00:18:16,680 --> 00:18:18,800
Even if traditional Xuan paper is to die out,

413
00:18:18,800 --> 00:18:20,400
it absolutely won't be on my watch.

414
00:18:20,400 --> 00:18:23,560
What I'm doing is rebirth through fire,

415
00:18:23,560 --> 00:18:25,680
phoenix rising, dead wood blooming again.

416
00:18:26,800 --> 00:18:28,040
Add another idiom.

417
00:18:29,160 --> 00:18:30,200
I'm not educated enough.

418
00:18:30,800 --> 00:18:32,000
See, you can't add one either.

419
00:18:32,000 --> 00:18:33,320
As the old saying goes...

420
00:18:34,040 --> 00:18:35,520
Aren't you going to pour me some water?

421
00:18:51,120 --> 00:18:51,920
Hold on a sec.

422
00:18:54,000 --> 00:18:54,800
Writing.

423
00:19:06,760 --> 00:19:07,640
Director Liao.

424
00:19:09,920 --> 00:19:12,160
I've revised the draft.

425
00:19:12,680 --> 00:19:13,680
Please review it.

426
00:19:16,400 --> 00:19:18,160
If it's done, why would I review?

427
00:19:19,160 --> 00:19:21,640
It still has flaws. Please advise.

428
00:19:34,320 --> 00:19:35,920
You call this revised?

429
00:19:36,600 --> 00:19:38,920
You're missing the whole point.

430
00:19:39,160 --> 00:19:41,000
Penny-wise and pound-foolish.

431
00:19:45,840 --> 00:19:48,400
Then please tell me what's wrong.

432
00:19:48,400 --> 00:19:49,920
And I'll revise it again.

433
00:19:50,840 --> 00:19:52,160
Problems everywhere.

434
00:19:53,160 --> 00:19:54,720
Sheer nonsense on every page.

435
00:19:55,840 --> 00:19:58,680
Where's the town leaders' vision?

436
00:19:58,680 --> 00:20:01,640
Where are the national policies?

437
00:20:01,640 --> 00:20:03,680
Where are the city leaders' expectations,

438
00:20:03,920 --> 00:20:06,880
not your smug self-promotion.

439
00:20:07,480 --> 00:20:08,920
A perfectly fine draft of mine,

440
00:20:08,920 --> 00:20:10,560
edited by you to be sloppy,

441
00:20:10,760 --> 00:20:11,480
unserious,

442
00:20:11,480 --> 00:20:12,320
and shallow.

443
00:20:12,880 --> 00:20:14,200
Take it back and rewrite it now.

444
00:20:18,080 --> 00:20:19,240
How should I rewrite it?

445
00:20:19,640 --> 00:20:20,880
How about this, Director Liao?

446
00:20:20,880 --> 00:20:23,400
Just give me a rough direction.

447
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:25,960
You think you wrote it well, huh?

448
00:20:25,960 --> 00:20:26,920
No, I don't.

449
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:28,480
Writing an article

450
00:20:28,600 --> 00:20:30,320
is just about laying out the full story

451
00:20:30,320 --> 00:20:31,480
clearly, isn't it?

452
00:20:31,640 --> 00:20:33,400
Are you teaching me how to write?

453
00:20:34,360 --> 00:20:36,240
When I was publishing in newspapers,

454
00:20:36,640 --> 00:20:39,680
you were still learning vowels in kindergarten.

455
00:20:39,760 --> 00:20:40,840
Take it back and rewrite it.

456
00:20:43,920 --> 00:20:45,920
Secretary Peng assigned this to me.

457
00:20:46,080 --> 00:20:47,600
I'll send it to her for review.

458
00:20:47,600 --> 00:20:48,560
And go with her opinion.

459
00:20:48,560 --> 00:20:50,000
You're sending it to Secretary Peng?

460
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:51,560
Then why bother showing me?

461
00:21:03,080 --> 00:21:04,720
What have I always taught you?

462
00:21:05,240 --> 00:21:07,120
It's just a press release.

463
00:21:07,320 --> 00:21:08,240
If Director Liao wants changes,

464
00:21:08,240 --> 00:21:09,320
just revise it his way.

465
00:21:09,320 --> 00:21:10,800
Just find a middle ground.

466
00:21:10,960 --> 00:21:12,200
You're not doing literary creation,

467
00:21:12,200 --> 00:21:13,280
aiming for the Mao Dun Literature Prize.

468
00:21:13,280 --> 00:21:14,760
Why butt heads with him?

469
00:21:15,960 --> 00:21:17,360
I'm not butting heads with him.

470
00:21:17,600 --> 00:21:18,520
You're not?

471
00:21:18,520 --> 00:21:20,160
Then why rush it to Secretary Peng?

472
00:21:20,680 --> 00:21:23,200
What if Secretary Peng says it's great?

473
00:21:23,200 --> 00:21:24,240
That's not good either.

474
00:21:25,880 --> 00:21:26,680
Look at this.

475
00:21:27,160 --> 00:21:28,760
Secretary Peng said it's great.

476
00:21:28,760 --> 00:21:30,880
She told Director Liao to publish it.

477
00:21:31,240 --> 00:21:32,080
Great.

478
00:21:34,600 --> 00:21:35,400
You're done for.

479
00:21:36,320 --> 00:21:38,920
You've completely offended Old Liao.

480
00:21:39,680 --> 00:21:40,960
So what if I offended him?

481
00:21:40,960 --> 00:21:42,000
What else could I do?

482
00:21:42,120 --> 00:21:43,000
You'll cross paths again.

483
00:21:43,000 --> 00:21:44,800
Unity matters, Lin Yiran.

484
00:21:45,400 --> 00:21:48,120
I admit, you're skilled at your job.

485
00:21:48,360 --> 00:21:49,760
But with your EQ,

486
00:21:49,880 --> 00:21:51,080
you won't survive three episodes.

487
00:21:53,160 --> 00:21:54,440
Honestly, let me tell you,

488
00:21:54,520 --> 00:21:56,160
when I was in the office,

489
00:21:56,160 --> 00:21:58,200
I'd already figured out what to do.

490
00:21:58,880 --> 00:22:00,240
But I just refused to do it.

491
00:22:00,880 --> 00:22:01,880
I wanted to piss him off.

492
00:22:04,920 --> 00:22:07,440
Lin Yiran, you're hopeless.

493
00:22:17,160 --> 00:22:20,680
So pounding the bark breaks down

494
00:22:20,680 --> 00:22:22,080
the fibers of the green sandalwood bark, right?

495
00:22:22,080 --> 00:22:22,880
That's right.

496
00:22:23,920 --> 00:22:25,960
This is just one of the steps

497
00:22:25,960 --> 00:22:27,480
before the pulping process.

498
00:22:27,480 --> 00:22:30,160
After this, we cut the bark, trample it,

499
00:22:30,160 --> 00:22:31,680
soak it overnight, and so on.

500
00:22:31,720 --> 00:22:34,480
Making Xuan paper takes 108 steps in total.

501
00:22:34,840 --> 00:22:36,600
Dozens of steps come before

502
00:22:36,640 --> 00:22:38,120
we even reach this pounding stage.

503
00:22:38,120 --> 00:22:39,440
Couldn't you just use machines?

504
00:22:39,440 --> 00:22:40,480
This is so slow.

505
00:22:40,800 --> 00:22:42,600
Yeah, like a soy milk maker.

506
00:22:42,600 --> 00:22:43,840
Just buzz it all up.

507
00:22:45,240 --> 00:22:47,000
You two really know how to slack off.

508
00:22:47,120 --> 00:22:50,080
Sure, doing it your way would be fast,

509
00:22:50,280 --> 00:22:53,440
but it would shred the fibers of the bark,

510
00:22:53,520 --> 00:22:55,480
and the paper would lose tensile strength.

511
00:22:55,960 --> 00:22:56,760
I get it.

512
00:22:56,760 --> 00:22:58,120
It's like cutting the materials by hand

513
00:22:58,120 --> 00:23:00,120
to preserve the fiber length.

514
00:23:00,120 --> 00:23:00,760
Exactly.

515
00:23:01,360 --> 00:23:04,280
These were all improvements made later.

516
00:23:04,520 --> 00:23:06,440
Personally, I still prefer

517
00:23:06,440 --> 00:23:08,120
pounding the bark and materials by hand.

518
00:23:08,200 --> 00:23:10,440
That way you can really feel

519
00:23:10,480 --> 00:23:12,200
the warmth of the materials.

520
00:23:12,600 --> 00:23:14,480
Only craftsmen like you could say that.

521
00:23:14,480 --> 00:23:15,720
If I had to do this work,

522
00:23:15,720 --> 00:23:17,960
I'd go nuts within three days.

523
00:23:18,560 --> 00:23:19,360
Look at this.

524
00:23:19,360 --> 00:23:20,880
Doesn't this look like dried bamboo shoots?

525
00:23:21,720 --> 00:23:22,680
It really does.

526
00:23:24,000 --> 00:23:26,560
My old teacher in traditional restoration

527
00:23:26,680 --> 00:23:27,920
used to always tell me,

528
00:23:28,320 --> 00:23:30,720
"Traditions lie with the craftsman."

529
00:23:31,000 --> 00:23:34,080
Better to stay humble than to cut corners.

530
00:23:40,080 --> 00:23:42,160
Look at how these couplets are designed now.

531
00:23:42,400 --> 00:23:43,840
You don't even need glue.

532
00:23:44,360 --> 00:23:45,400
So much more convenient.

533
00:23:46,400 --> 00:23:48,200
How do you not know anything?

534
00:23:48,440 --> 00:23:50,200
They sell these online.

535
00:23:50,200 --> 00:23:51,560
A dozen yuan a pair.

536
00:23:52,320 --> 00:23:53,080
That expensive?

537
00:23:53,080 --> 00:23:55,200
I only get a few yuan for five pairs.

538
00:23:55,200 --> 00:23:57,080
There's just no way to make a living.

539
00:24:00,440 --> 00:24:01,680
Have you guys heard?

540
00:24:01,840 --> 00:24:03,920
Daya Studio and Xuan Yongnian's

541
00:24:04,080 --> 00:24:06,000
The Xuan paper notebooks are selling fast.

542
00:24:06,000 --> 00:24:07,560
Lots of factories are placing orders.

543
00:24:07,560 --> 00:24:09,320
Who doesn't know that?

544
00:24:09,400 --> 00:24:11,760
Lin Yiran from the Dev Office set this up.

545
00:24:12,160 --> 00:24:13,080
And I also know

546
00:24:13,080 --> 00:24:15,480
Secretary Peng is helping promote it too.

547
00:24:15,640 --> 00:24:17,880
The town supports private businesses,

548
00:24:17,920 --> 00:24:19,600
but it can't just support those two.

549
00:24:19,600 --> 00:24:20,760
What about the rest of us?

550
00:24:20,880 --> 00:24:22,960
The government isn't run by the Xuan family.

551
00:24:22,960 --> 00:24:24,840
Shouldn't we all get a share?

552
00:24:24,920 --> 00:24:25,680
For this matter,

553
00:24:26,360 --> 00:24:28,880
Boss Xiao needs to tell Secretary Peng.

554
00:24:29,560 --> 00:24:30,200
Let's go.

555
00:24:31,400 --> 00:24:32,160
Old Xiao.

556
00:24:34,360 --> 00:24:36,000
The orders for the Xuan paper notebooks,

557
00:24:36,000 --> 00:24:37,680
Daya Studio gave them all to the Xuan family.

558
00:24:37,680 --> 00:24:39,680
You need to bring this up with Secretary Peng.

559
00:24:39,760 --> 00:24:41,880
This kind of favoritism isn't right.

560
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:43,680
Boss Xiao, you're our association chairman.

561
00:24:44,120 --> 00:24:45,400
You're the one who has to speak up.

562
00:24:46,640 --> 00:24:48,880
Fine, let me look into it first.

563
00:24:50,640 --> 00:24:53,160
Only Chairman Xiao can handle this.

564
00:24:53,160 --> 00:24:53,880
Get lost!

565
00:25:00,920 --> 00:25:02,880
High quality really makes a difference.

566
00:25:03,560 --> 00:25:04,360
Master Qian.

567
00:25:06,960 --> 00:25:07,720
Take a look.

568
00:25:07,720 --> 00:25:09,240
Why is the ink bleeding a bit?

569
00:25:09,240 --> 00:25:11,400
The finished product can't have a single flaw.

570
00:25:11,440 --> 00:25:12,880
I'll go tell the printing workshop.

571
00:25:12,880 --> 00:25:13,440
This batch,

572
00:25:13,440 --> 00:25:15,360
I'll sort them out and scrap them all.

573
00:25:15,440 --> 00:25:15,880
Go now.

574
00:25:15,880 --> 00:25:16,280
Okay.

575
00:25:18,400 --> 00:25:20,600
Mr. Xin, your quality control

576
00:25:20,600 --> 00:25:21,840
is really strict.

577
00:25:21,840 --> 00:25:23,240
That's something I should learn from.

578
00:25:23,240 --> 00:25:24,880
You're not here to learn from me, are you?

579
00:25:25,240 --> 00:25:26,920
If you've got something to say, just say it.

580
00:25:27,280 --> 00:25:28,080
Alright.

581
00:25:28,200 --> 00:25:30,240
Secretary Peng gave the conference notebook order

582
00:25:30,240 --> 00:25:31,880
all to you, right?

583
00:25:32,320 --> 00:25:35,160
I've got a few small business friends

584
00:25:35,600 --> 00:25:37,200
who'd like a piece of the action too.

585
00:25:37,360 --> 00:25:38,480
I went to the Secretary,

586
00:25:38,560 --> 00:25:41,000
and he told me to come discuss it with you.

587
00:25:41,160 --> 00:25:42,240
So today I'm here,

588
00:25:42,480 --> 00:25:44,640
first, to learn from you,

589
00:25:45,080 --> 00:25:48,240
and second, to humbly ask you

590
00:25:48,600 --> 00:25:50,400
to show some sympathy for everyone.

591
00:25:51,200 --> 00:25:54,120
Have the meat, let them have some broth.

592
00:25:54,440 --> 00:25:55,480
Not a big order,

593
00:25:55,840 --> 00:25:56,840
just a little will do.

594
00:25:56,920 --> 00:25:58,720
When you were all feasting on meat and wine,

595
00:25:58,840 --> 00:26:00,120
I didn't see you share a bite with me.

596
00:26:00,160 --> 00:26:02,360
You can't put it that way, Mr. Xin.

597
00:26:02,360 --> 00:26:03,480
If we were really feasting every meal,

598
00:26:03,480 --> 00:26:04,680
wouldn't that be great?

599
00:26:04,680 --> 00:26:05,400
Right?

600
00:26:07,200 --> 00:26:09,200
Don't get me wrong,

601
00:26:09,400 --> 00:26:11,360
it's not that we won't share orders.

602
00:26:11,840 --> 00:26:13,840
Our orders really are too small.

603
00:26:14,080 --> 00:26:16,200
I feared a big company wouldn't bother.

604
00:26:17,000 --> 00:26:17,840
How about this:

605
00:26:17,960 --> 00:26:19,920
Tonight, my treat.

606
00:26:20,240 --> 00:26:22,960
Let me treat you to the most authentic

607
00:26:23,360 --> 00:26:24,600
authentic local dishes.

608
00:26:25,320 --> 00:26:26,680
Then I'll find a few friends

609
00:26:26,760 --> 00:26:27,960
to have a few drinks with you.

610
00:26:28,400 --> 00:26:29,440
Alright, you go on with your work.

611
00:26:29,560 --> 00:26:31,160
I'll go book a room right now.

612
00:26:31,160 --> 00:26:32,760
Once it's booked, I'll call you.

613
00:26:33,400 --> 00:26:34,440
Mr. Xiao, Mr. Xiao.

614
00:26:36,240 --> 00:26:38,200
The dinner's not necessary.

615
00:26:39,320 --> 00:26:41,680
But there's one thing I must make clear.

616
00:26:41,680 --> 00:26:42,320
Go ahead.

617
00:26:42,320 --> 00:26:43,480
As for me,

618
00:26:43,680 --> 00:26:45,000
I don't care about the size of the order,

619
00:26:45,000 --> 00:26:48,000
but I do care about product quality.

620
00:26:48,360 --> 00:26:49,680
My factory's motto

621
00:26:50,000 --> 00:26:53,360
is "No quality, no future".

622
00:26:53,480 --> 00:26:54,320
Every product

623
00:26:54,320 --> 00:26:56,600
must go through initial, secondary, and spot checks.

624
00:26:56,680 --> 00:26:58,600
Can they manage that?

625
00:27:02,400 --> 00:27:04,080
Mr. Xin, would you reconsider?

626
00:27:04,080 --> 00:27:07,120
Mr. Xiao, I'm truly sorry.

627
00:27:07,880 --> 00:27:08,880
This order,

628
00:27:09,920 --> 00:27:10,880
I can't share it.

629
00:27:11,920 --> 00:27:14,080
Why do you get so serious whenever it's about work?

630
00:27:14,080 --> 00:27:15,160
No, being serious about work is the right thing.

631
00:27:15,160 --> 00:27:16,080
Master Qian, Master Li.

632
00:27:16,480 --> 00:27:18,080
That batch of products just now,

633
00:27:18,200 --> 00:27:19,840
they really can't be used.

634
00:27:48,160 --> 00:27:48,960
Old Xuan

635
00:27:50,320 --> 00:27:53,680
This notebook business is a great deal

636
00:27:54,080 --> 00:27:56,320
Just by supplying xuan paper

637
00:27:56,480 --> 00:27:58,200
for these notebooks

638
00:27:58,680 --> 00:28:01,600
the factory's profits will go up

639
00:28:02,960 --> 00:28:04,240
This business is worth doing

640
00:28:08,280 --> 00:28:11,520
But what I'm afraid of is

641
00:28:12,240 --> 00:28:13,280
it won't last

642
00:28:13,920 --> 00:28:15,080
Around this town nowadays

643
00:28:15,080 --> 00:28:17,080
plenty of folks are green with envy.

644
00:28:25,320 --> 00:28:26,000
What's going on?

645
00:28:26,160 --> 00:28:27,000
Everyone come over, gather up!

646
00:28:27,000 --> 00:28:27,680
Everyone gather up!

647
00:28:27,680 --> 00:28:29,600
Today we must get an explanation

648
00:28:29,760 --> 00:28:31,040
Let's go to Secretary Peng for justice

649
00:28:31,120 --> 00:28:32,840
All you bosses, come over, gather up

650
00:28:32,920 --> 00:28:33,560
Everyone gather up

651
00:28:33,560 --> 00:28:35,400
Today we must get an explanation

652
00:28:35,400 --> 00:28:36,560
Right, find Secretary Peng

653
00:28:37,360 --> 00:28:37,760
This is bad!

654
00:28:38,400 --> 00:28:39,000
This is bad!

655
00:28:39,320 --> 00:28:41,480
Erhu and those paper mill bosses are here

656
00:28:41,640 --> 00:28:42,440
There's a whole crowd

657
00:28:42,600 --> 00:28:43,840
I think they're here to cause trouble

658
00:28:44,280 --> 00:28:45,240
What did I tell you?

659
00:28:45,440 --> 00:28:46,280
Weren't you so clever?

660
00:28:46,640 --> 00:28:47,840
Let's see what you do now

661
00:28:49,440 --> 00:28:50,600
I'll handle it however it needs to be handled

662
00:28:51,840 --> 00:28:53,360
Let's see how long you can stay stubborn

663
00:28:53,360 --> 00:28:54,680
Director, stop scolding her for now

664
00:28:55,240 --> 00:28:57,160
Yiran, has Xiao Min approached you?

665
00:28:58,000 --> 00:28:59,640
He didn't approach me, he went to Xuan Yan

666
00:28:59,640 --> 00:29:01,400
Asking him to authorize the Xuan Paper Association

667
00:29:01,400 --> 00:29:02,160
Xuan Yan didn't agree

668
00:29:02,160 --> 00:29:02,960
You go tell Xuan Yan

669
00:29:02,960 --> 00:29:04,280
to share part of the orders

670
00:29:04,280 --> 00:29:05,200
with the Xuan Paper Association

671
00:29:06,960 --> 00:29:08,800
Those bosses in Xiao Min's association

672
00:29:08,920 --> 00:29:11,400
keep lowering quality and slashing prices

673
00:29:11,520 --> 00:29:13,560
driving traditional Xuan makers to ruin.

674
00:29:13,560 --> 00:29:14,720
Do you think such people deserve help?

675
00:29:16,480 --> 00:29:18,680
If this matter isn't handled well

676
00:29:19,440 --> 00:29:20,800
not only will you not get promoted

677
00:29:21,840 --> 00:29:24,440
whether you can keep your civil servant job

678
00:29:25,320 --> 00:29:26,520
is not even certain

679
00:29:27,680 --> 00:29:28,200
Enough

680
00:29:30,400 --> 00:29:31,200
Director Liao

681
00:29:31,760 --> 00:29:32,480
That's enough, Director Liao

682
00:29:32,480 --> 00:29:33,560
Don't you go, I'll go

683
00:29:34,920 --> 00:29:35,760
You get back inside

684
00:29:36,720 --> 00:29:37,560
and stay put

685
00:29:40,800 --> 00:29:41,600
Director Liao

686
00:29:41,760 --> 00:29:42,440
Director Liao

687
00:29:42,440 --> 00:29:42,960
You can't go out there

688
00:29:42,960 --> 00:29:44,080
They're coming for you

689
00:29:44,080 --> 00:29:45,160
Go back, Yiran

690
00:29:45,160 --> 00:29:45,760
Liao

691
00:29:45,880 --> 00:29:47,040
It's nothing

692
00:29:47,560 --> 00:29:50,880
Erhu, just talk it out calmly, alright?

693
00:29:50,880 --> 00:29:51,800
What are you trying to do?

694
00:29:51,960 --> 00:29:53,400
Impulse is the devil.

695
00:29:53,400 --> 00:29:55,000
Everyone, calm down first

696
00:29:55,000 --> 00:29:56,000
All talking over each other

697
00:29:56,000 --> 00:29:57,320
With everyone shouting like this

698
00:29:57,320 --> 00:29:58,520
how can we solve anything?

699
00:29:58,520 --> 00:30:00,200
Let's all head to the meeting room

700
00:30:00,200 --> 00:30:01,560
We'll sit down and talk this through

701
00:30:01,760 --> 00:30:04,000
This notebook business was Lin Yiran's doing

702
00:30:04,040 --> 00:30:05,160
Bring Lin Yiran out

703
00:30:05,160 --> 00:30:06,240
She owes us an explanation

704
00:30:06,240 --> 00:30:07,560
Right, bring Lin Yiran out

705
00:30:07,800 --> 00:30:11,080
Bring Lin Yiran out

706
00:30:11,080 --> 00:30:12,200
Call her out here

707
00:30:12,200 --> 00:30:12,840
I'm right here

708
00:30:16,880 --> 00:30:17,760
Lin Yiran is here.

709
00:30:19,640 --> 00:30:20,160
No need.

710
00:30:23,160 --> 00:30:24,800
Truly someone back from the capital.

711
00:30:25,520 --> 00:30:26,320
Impressive.

712
00:30:27,040 --> 00:30:28,080
We just want to ask,

713
00:30:28,400 --> 00:30:29,600
this notebook order,

714
00:30:29,600 --> 00:30:31,400
why didn't it go through the Association,

715
00:30:31,400 --> 00:30:32,920
and went straight to the Xuan family?

716
00:30:33,040 --> 00:30:34,720
You owe us a satisfying answer.

717
00:30:34,760 --> 00:30:37,080
Otherwise, we'll go to the county, the city,

718
00:30:37,080 --> 00:30:38,360
or the province to demand an answer.

719
00:30:38,360 --> 00:30:38,720
Right.

720
00:30:38,720 --> 00:30:39,760
This notebook,

721
00:30:39,760 --> 00:30:41,520
Xuan Yan is the original designer.

722
00:30:41,520 --> 00:30:43,600
Who he gives it to is his right.

723
00:30:43,680 --> 00:30:44,560
If you have something to say,

724
00:30:44,560 --> 00:30:45,920
just go ask him directly, right?

725
00:30:46,200 --> 00:30:46,800
You say that,

726
00:30:46,800 --> 00:30:48,240
you washed your hands of it pretty cleanly.

727
00:30:48,960 --> 00:30:50,280
You think we're fools?

728
00:30:50,560 --> 00:30:51,560
Everyone knows

729
00:30:51,680 --> 00:30:53,560
you were the one who urged Secretary Peng

730
00:30:53,560 --> 00:30:54,840
to bring orders to their family.

731
00:30:55,200 --> 00:30:56,400
The whole town knows

732
00:30:56,560 --> 00:30:59,720
you've been getting awfully close to Xuan Yan lately.

733
00:31:00,320 --> 00:31:01,680
One sets the stage, the other performs.

734
00:31:01,760 --> 00:31:04,320
You're funneling benefits to your in-laws!

735
00:31:04,320 --> 00:31:05,240
Don't you spout nonsense at me.

736
00:31:05,240 --> 00:31:07,320
Erhu, you'd better stand by your words.

737
00:31:07,520 --> 00:31:09,600
No matter how you slander or smear me,

738
00:31:09,600 --> 00:31:11,000
I can let it slide.

739
00:31:11,080 --> 00:31:13,240
But please, think for yourselves,

740
00:31:14,680 --> 00:31:16,680
how many of you here

741
00:31:17,080 --> 00:31:19,640
are deliberately cutting corners,

742
00:31:19,640 --> 00:31:20,680
maliciously slashing prices.

743
00:31:20,720 --> 00:31:22,280
It's this kind of chaotic competition

744
00:31:22,280 --> 00:31:24,680
that put our industry in such a state.

745
00:31:24,840 --> 00:31:26,560
Many Xuan paper mills in Taohua Town

746
00:31:27,080 --> 00:31:29,240
were passed down for centuries.

747
00:31:29,560 --> 00:31:31,040
Your ancestors left you

748
00:31:31,040 --> 00:31:31,960
such a great livelihood.

749
00:31:31,960 --> 00:31:32,720
And you?

750
00:31:32,800 --> 00:31:33,920
What are you leaving

751
00:31:33,920 --> 00:31:35,200
for your descendants?

752
00:31:36,080 --> 00:31:37,520
You'd better make yourself clear!

753
00:31:37,520 --> 00:31:39,720
Who's cutting corners? Who's competing chaotically?

754
00:31:39,720 --> 00:31:40,720
Who? You tell me who!

755
00:31:40,720 --> 00:31:41,960
Spell it out clearly!

756
00:31:44,520 --> 00:31:46,360
Everyone, please calm down.

757
00:31:46,440 --> 00:31:48,240
In a bit, let's head to the meeting room

758
00:31:48,240 --> 00:31:49,240
and talk it through in detail.

759
00:31:51,520 --> 00:31:52,640
Old Xuan.

760
00:31:54,560 --> 00:31:55,320
Old Xuan.

761
00:31:57,960 --> 00:32:00,880
That Erhu ran into town to stir up trouble.

762
00:32:01,040 --> 00:32:02,320
He's telling everyone

763
00:32:02,400 --> 00:32:04,680
that Lin Yiran is shielding our Xuan family.

764
00:32:06,520 --> 00:32:07,680
Old Zhu, take care of this.

765
00:32:07,680 --> 00:32:08,360
Let's go.

766
00:32:08,800 --> 00:32:09,560
Secretary Peng

767
00:32:10,840 --> 00:32:13,240
is being scolded by county higher-ups now.

768
00:32:13,640 --> 00:32:15,040
She called and said

769
00:32:15,360 --> 00:32:18,320
today's situation must be properly resolved.

770
00:32:18,440 --> 00:32:19,680
If things escalate,

771
00:32:19,840 --> 00:32:22,760
no one responsible will escape blame.

772
00:32:24,080 --> 00:32:25,360
This time we're really done for.

773
00:32:25,840 --> 00:32:26,600
Lin Yiran,

774
00:32:26,600 --> 00:32:29,080
if you don't handle this well,

775
00:32:29,320 --> 00:32:31,080
you'll never get promoted.

776
00:32:35,200 --> 00:32:36,000
Director Liao,

777
00:32:36,600 --> 00:32:39,080
I know you think I like grabbing the spotlight,

778
00:32:39,160 --> 00:32:41,000
seeking advancement, wanting to climb up.

779
00:32:41,440 --> 00:32:42,840
But I really don't.

780
00:32:43,240 --> 00:32:44,840
I just believe if something

781
00:32:44,840 --> 00:32:47,000
can be done well, it should be done to the best.

782
00:32:47,560 --> 00:32:49,360
Do right by everyone, do right by yourself.

783
00:32:49,360 --> 00:32:50,440
That's not wrong.

784
00:32:54,600 --> 00:32:55,440
Who is it?

785
00:32:55,440 --> 00:32:55,920
Me.

786
00:32:59,040 --> 00:33:00,280
Did you call Xiao Min?

787
00:33:01,040 --> 00:33:01,800
Call?

788
00:33:01,800 --> 00:33:02,720
What call?

789
00:33:02,840 --> 00:33:04,320
Xiao Min called Secretary Peng,

790
00:33:04,320 --> 00:33:06,120
said he can't control the situation,

791
00:33:06,440 --> 00:33:07,760
and is requesting to resign.

792
00:33:08,000 --> 00:33:09,520
He's just playing dumb.

793
00:33:09,760 --> 00:33:11,920
He bears responsibility for this matter.

794
00:33:12,080 --> 00:33:13,920
No, this can't be delayed any longer.

795
00:33:14,160 --> 00:33:16,000
With Secretary Peng away, I'll take charge.

796
00:33:16,080 --> 00:33:17,240
Sit down, everyone, sit down.

797
00:33:19,600 --> 00:33:23,040
Contact Xuan Yan, Xin Ran,

798
00:33:23,040 --> 00:33:24,360
and Xiao Min right away. Get them all here.

799
00:33:24,360 --> 00:33:26,120
We'll figure out how to distribute orders.

800
00:33:26,120 --> 00:33:27,400
No matter what, today

801
00:33:27,800 --> 00:33:28,840
we have to work out

802
00:33:28,840 --> 00:33:30,360
a result that satisfies all parties.

803
00:33:30,560 --> 00:33:32,160
All Erhu's bickering

804
00:33:32,680 --> 00:33:33,880
boils down to one word: profit.

805
00:33:33,880 --> 00:33:36,280
If Xuan Yan shares some orders with them,

806
00:33:36,360 --> 00:33:37,840
wouldn't everything be settled?

807
00:33:38,880 --> 00:33:41,080
Lin Yiran, give Xuan Yan a call.

808
00:33:51,280 --> 00:33:52,920
What? Not picking up?

809
00:33:53,440 --> 00:33:55,360
I just called him and he wouldn't answer.

810
00:33:55,560 --> 00:33:56,440
What's Xuan Yan trying to pull?

811
00:33:56,600 --> 00:33:57,840
Wants to hog it all for himself?

812
00:33:58,120 --> 00:34:00,440
When the crucial moment comes, he backs off.

813
00:34:00,760 --> 00:34:02,280
Xuan Yan is so unreliable.

814
00:34:02,520 --> 00:34:03,920
Drops the ball when it matters most.

815
00:34:04,560 --> 00:34:05,360
Come on now.

816
00:34:05,760 --> 00:34:07,200
He's so strict about craftsmanship.

817
00:34:07,280 --> 00:34:09,280
How could he share orders with Erhu?

818
00:34:09,280 --> 00:34:10,560
But he can't just wash his hands of it.

819
00:34:10,560 --> 00:34:11,600
Leaving you to carry it all.

820
00:34:12,040 --> 00:34:14,600
Yiran, I'm afraid you'll have to suck it up.

821
00:34:15,000 --> 00:34:16,679
Go and apologize to them.

822
00:34:16,880 --> 00:34:18,760
First, calm them down.

823
00:34:18,800 --> 00:34:20,800
We can solve things step by step.

824
00:34:20,800 --> 00:34:22,400
But today, no matter what,

825
00:34:22,400 --> 00:34:25,000
we can't let this blow up any further.

826
00:34:25,840 --> 00:34:27,480
I think at this point,

827
00:34:27,480 --> 00:34:29,320
there's nothing left to consider.

828
00:34:29,679 --> 00:34:32,880
The county leaders are taking this very seriously.

829
00:34:33,120 --> 00:34:34,880
If we don't resolve this today,

830
00:34:35,080 --> 00:34:36,760
everyone here will be held responsible.

831
00:34:36,920 --> 00:34:38,280
Including Secretary Peng.

832
00:34:39,120 --> 00:34:40,600
Who can shoulder that?

833
00:34:40,600 --> 00:34:42,120
Who gets the order, who doesn't,

834
00:34:42,440 --> 00:34:44,360
